{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783278264,"nonce":"4VJYnCv76HJiPrIORz+0TuDsDQE=","message":"Shipped in PR #80 (squash 0f4e038). Query-only, single named window, with the confirmed **typed-handle** API:\n\n    db.from::\u003cSales\u003e()\n        .window(|(s,)| Window::new().partition_by(s.region).order_by(s.day.asc()))\n        .select_over(|(s,), w| (s.amount.sum().over_ref(w), s.amount.avg().over_ref(w)));\n    // SELECT SUM(amount) OVER w0, AVG(amount) OVER w0\n    //   FROM sales WINDOW w0 AS (PARTITION BY region ORDER BY day ASC)\n\n- `.window(|cols| Window::new()...)` declares the window (returns `WindowScope`); `.select_over(|cols, w| ...)` finishes the query, passing a zero-size `WindowRef` handle so `over_ref(w)` can only name a declared window. `WindowBy` is a new `SelectAst` link rendered after HAVING / before ORDER BY (new `lower_windows_into` step + `SelectSink::push_named_window` + `ExprVisitor::visit_named_window`). Shared `SelectRenderSink` (PG/MySQL/SQLite) + `TestSelectSink`. Gated to a new `SupportsNamedWindow` marker (PG, MySQL 8.0+, SQLite 3.25+); NOT the view-model backend, so a named window in a view body is a compile error.\n\n**Codex: 6 rounds, 6 real findings, all fixed** — every one a soundness hole in the compile-time proof that `OVER w0` can't render without its `WINDOW w0` clause:\n1. `WindowRef` given an invariant `'brand` lifetime + `for\u003c'brand\u003e` closure so the handle can't escape (compile-fail test).\n2. CTEs referenced inside a window def's PARTITION BY/ORDER BY are now collected into the `WITH` prefix.\n3. A `CONTAINS_NAMED_WINDOW` const guard rejects a stashed `over_ref` expression projected by a plain `select`/`select_correlated`/`project`/`select_subquery`.\n4. The flag is folded through the **entire** expression AND predicate AST (a named window nests via `+`, CASE/NULLIF/EXTRACT, and searched-CASE WHEN comparisons).\n5. `order_by` guarded too; HAVING/GROUP BY/WHERE/JOIN ON/RETURNING already reject named windows, set-op ORDER BY is column-only, UPDATE/INSERT reject by construction.\n\n**Deferred (documented, candidates for a follow-up if pursued):**\n- **Multiple distinct named windows** (`WINDOW w0 …, w1 …`) — an HList of handles. Single-window covers the bug's example (one window, many references).\n- **View support** — `ViewQueryModel.window_definitions` + `view.rs`/`view_render.rs` lowering + squealy-model KDL round-trip. Currently compile-time-gated out of view bodies.\n- **Known limitation** (uncatchable in the single-window positional form without an API redesign): deliberately stashing an `over_ref` expression out of its `select_over` closure and reusing it in a *different* `select_over` binds it to that query's window. Documented on `over_ref`; the invalid-SQL variant (reuse where no window is declared) IS rejected at compile time.\n\nClosing: the named `WINDOW` clause is delivered and usable across all backends. The deferred items above are enhancements, not part of the core ask.","files":null}]}